Budworm Data

budworm.Rd

Venables and Ripley (2002) state: "Collett (1991, p. 75) reports an experiment on the toxicity to the tobacco budworm Heliothis virescens of doses of the pyrethroid trans-cypermethrin to which the moths were beginning to show resistance. Batches of 20 moths of each sex were exposed for three days to the pyrethroid and the number in each batch that were dead or knocked down was recorded."

Collett, D. (1991) Modelling Binary Data. London: Chapman & Hall.

Usage

budworm

Format

A data.frame with 12 rows and 4 columns: –

ldose

Dose of the pyrethroid trans-cypermethrin.

sex

Sex of the budworm.

numdead

Number that were dead or knocked down.

numalive

Number that were alive.

Source

W.N. Venables and B.D. Ripley (2002). Modern Applied Statistics with S. Fourth Edition 2002. Statistics and Computing, © 2002 Springer Science+Business Media New York. doi:10.1007/978-0-387-21706-2 . Chapter 7: Generalized Linear Models, p. 190.
